import scipy.stats as stats
import pandas as pd
import researchpy as rp
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import statsmodels.stats.multicomp as mc
from statsmodels.formula.api import ols
import warnings

# Supress unwanted errors from script output
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore", category=FutureWarning)

# Import data from csv
df = pd.read_csv("/workspaces/codespaces-blank/research-data.csv")
# Drop ID column to deidentify
df.drop("ID", axis=1, inplace=True)
# (Optional) Set criteria for age filter
df = df[df['Age'] < 6.0]

def GeneratePlots(frame, dcol, icol, dvlabel="Dependent Variable", ivlabel="Independent Variable"):
    def anova_table(aov):
        aov['mean_sq'] = aov[:]['sum_sq'] / aov[:]['df']
        aov['eta_sq'] = aov[:-1]['sum_sq'] / sum(aov['sum_sq'])
        aov['omega_sq'] = (aov[:-1]['sum_sq'] - (aov[:-1]['df'] * aov['mean_sq'][-1])) / (sum(aov['sum_sq']) + aov['mean_sq'][-1])
        cols = ["sum_sq", "df", "mean_sq", "F", "PR(>F)", "eta_sq", "omega_sq"]
        aov = aov[cols]
        return aov


    # Initialize Global Variables
    dv = frame.get(dcol)
    iv = frame.get(icol)
    ivals = iv.unique().tolist()
    model = ols(f"{dcol} ~ C({icol})", data=df).fit()
    aov_table = sm.stats.anova_lm(model, typ=2)

    # Generate Probability Plot
    prob_fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))
    prob_ax = prob_fig.add_subplot(111)
    normality_plot, stat = stats.probplot(model.resid, plot=plt, rvalue=True)
    prob_ax.set_title(f"Probability Plot of {ivlabel} Residuals")
    prob_ax.set
    plt.show()

    # Generate Box Plot
    box_fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))
    box_ax = box_fig.add_subplot(111)
    box_ax.set_title(f"Box Plot of {dvlabel} by {ivlabel}", fontsize=20)
    box_ax.set
    data = [dv[iv == i] for i in ivals]
    box_ax.boxplot(data, tick_labels=ivals, showmeans=True)
    plt.xlabel(ivlabel)
    plt.ylabel(dvlabel)
    plt.show()

    # Generate Tukey HSD Table
    comp = mc.MultiComparison(dv, iv)
    post_hoc_res = comp.tukeyhsd()
    post_hoc_res.plot_simultaneous(ylabel=dvlabel, xlabel="Score Difference")

    # Generate Bonferroni Table
    bonf_tbl, a1, a2 = comp.allpairtest(stats.ttest_ind, method="bonf")
    print(bonf_tbl)

    # Generate Sidak Table
    sidak_tbl, a1, a2 = comp.allpairtest(stats.ttest_ind, method="sidak")
    print(sidak_tbl)

    # Generate Supplementary Figures
    rp.summary_cont(dv).groupby(iv)
    print(anova_table(aov_table))   
    print(stats.f_oneway(*[dv[iv == i] for i in ivals]))
    print(stats.levene(*[dv[iv == i] for i in ivals]))
    print(stats.shapiro(model.resid))

    return


for variable in df.columns.tolist():
    if variable[0:2] == "e_" or variable == "Words_Per_Sentence" or variable == "Age" or variable == "s_AgeCat" :
        continue
    else:
        GeneratePlots(df, "Words_Per_Sentence", variable, "Words Per Sentence", variable.replace("_", " "))
